		<item>
		<title>
		By: Anon		</title>
		<link>https://wordcounter.net/blog/2016/10/05/102258_using-a-pseudonym.html#comments/41710</link>

		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Anon]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 07 May 2018 06:29:32 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://wordcounter.net/blog/?p=2258#comment-41710</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://wordcounter.net/blog/2016/10/05/102258_using-a-pseudonym.html#comments/11559&quot;&gt;Liniol&lt;/a&gt;.

Just because you think a certain way doesn’t mean everyone else does too. It has nothing to do with lack of pride. Some of us don’t want to be known for privacy reasons. 

I would never want to be famous. Seems awful to me. If there was a way to still share my talents with the world, but keep the attention away from myself, then that would be perfect. For example, if a book signing was part of the deal, i’d be out. I prefer a simple life.

I was a singer for a while, and a huge reason I stopped is because I didn’t like how more and more people were recognizing me from my performances. There is nothing like the thrill of performing, but I value anonymity even more than my biggest passion.

TL;DR I would rather be an unknown. Publishing under a pseudonym helps you keep unwanted attention away.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://wordcounter.net/blog/2016/10/05/102258_using-a-pseudonym.html#comments/11559">Liniol</a>.</p>
<p>Just because you think a certain way doesn’t mean everyone else does too. It has nothing to do with lack of pride. Some of us don’t want to be known for privacy reasons. </p>
<p>I would never want to be famous. Seems awful to me. If there was a way to still share my talents with the world, but keep the attention away from myself, then that would be perfect. For example, if a book signing was part of the deal, i’d be out. I prefer a simple life.</p>
<p>I was a singer for a while, and a huge reason I stopped is because I didn’t like how more and more people were recognizing me from my performances. There is nothing like the thrill of performing, but I value anonymity even more than my biggest passion.</p>
<p>TL;DR I would rather be an unknown. Publishing under a pseudonym helps you keep unwanted attention away.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
