There are a lot of legitimate reasons to use one as the article pointed out. Just because that happens to be your opinion doesn&#039;t make it true. There is nothing wrong if someone wants to use a pen name when writing for whatever reason they decide it&#039;s appropriate. That doesn&#039;t make them weak in any way.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://wordcounter.net/blog/2016/10/05/102258_using-a-pseudonym.html#comments/11559">Liniol</a>.</p>
<p>There are a lot of legitimate reasons to use one as the article pointed out. Just because that happens to be your opinion doesn&#8217;t make it true. There is nothing wrong if someone wants to use a pen name when writing for whatever reason they decide it&#8217;s appropriate. That doesn&#8217;t make them weak in any way.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
